sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as RHOAI Gateway<br/>Platform TLS / kube-rbac-proxy
    participant Server as NeMo Guardrails Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant InputRails as Input Rails<br/>(in-process)
    participant LLM as Upstream LLM Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OutputRails as Output Rails<br/>(in-process)
    participant OTel as OpenTelemetry Collector<br/>4317/TCP gRPC
    participant Redis as Redis (optional)<br/>6379/TCP

    Note over Client,Redis: Flow 1: Chat Completion with Guardrails

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Platform Auth
    Gateway->>Server: HTTP/8000<br/>Platform TLS terminated
    Server->>Redis: Load thread context (optional)
    Redis-->>Server: Thread history
    Server->>InputRails: Evaluate input guardrails<br/>(self-check, injection, PII, topic)
    InputRails-->>Server: Pass / Block

    alt Input Blocked
        Server-->>Gateway: 200 OK (blocked response)
        Gateway-->>Client: Guardrail rejection message
    else Input Passed
        Server->>LLM: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>Bearer Token (API key)
        LLM-->>Server: LLM Response
        Server->>OutputRails: Evaluate output guardrails<br/>(hallucination, fact-check, content safety)
        OutputRails-->>Server: Pass / Block / Modify
        Server->>Redis: Persist thread (optional)
        Server-->>Gateway: 200 OK (response)
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response
    end

    Server->>OTel: Export traces (OTLP)<br/>gRPC/4317 TLS

    Note over Client,Redis: Flow 2: Guardrail Check (No LLM Generation - IORails fast path)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/guardrail/checks<br/>Platform Auth
    Gateway->>Server: HTTP/8000
    Server->>InputRails: Evaluate rails only<br/>(no LLM call)
    InputRails-->>Server: Check results
    Server-->>Gateway: 200 OK (check results)
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Client,Redis: Flow 3: Model Listing (Passthrough)

    Client->>Gateway: GET /v1/models<br/>Authorization header
    Gateway->>Server: HTTP/8000
    Server->>LLM: GET /v1/models<br/>Forwarded Authorization header
    LLM-->>Server: Model list
    Server-->>Gateway: 200 OK
    Gateway-->>Client: Model list JSON
